  <brief_title>12 Week Evaluation of the Safety and Efficacy of a Flexible Dose of CP-526,555 and Placebo for Smoking Cessation</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Twelve-Week Double-Blind, Placebo-Controlled, Randomized, Multicenter Study Evaluating the Safety and Efficacy of a Flexible-Dosing Strategy for CP-526,555 ( 0.5 mg to 2.0 mg Total Daily Dose ) in Smoking Cessation</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Pfizer</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Pfizer</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study was to measure the safety and efficacy of a 12-week flexible dosing
      strategy of CP-526,555 compared with placebo for smoking cessation. Post-treatment follow-up
      of smoking status to one year from randomization was performed in a non-treatment extension
      Protocol A3051019
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
